    "created_at": "2019-02-18T11:44:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-02-18T11:44:04Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Just to add some more context on why it's not working:\r\n[`SetEnvironmentVariable(string variable, string value)`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.environment.setenvironmentvariable?view=netcore-2.2#System_Environment_SetEnvironmentVariable_System_String_System_String_System_EnvironmentVariableTarget_) is the overload for [`SetEnvironmentVariable (string variable, string value, EnvironmentVariableTarget target)`](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.environment.setenvironmentvariable?view=netcore-2.2#System_Environment_SetEnvironmentVariable_System_String_System_String_System_EnvironmentVariableTarget_) with `EnvironmentVariableTarget.Process`. So all changes using the simple call are in-process only. There are `EnvironmentVariableTarget` values for `Machine` and `User` too, but those are not supported on Linux/Mac and won't ever be due to technical limitations (see https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/issues/32685 & https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/issues/33745).\r\n\r\nI'm looking forward to have them in `GrpcEnvironment`."
